From: Apollo Linux Team <dev@apollolinux.org>
Subject: [PATCH 10/12] nvidia-390xx: fix seq_file overflow check (kernel 6.11)

Kernel 6.11 changed how seq_file overflow is detected.
The seq_has_overflowed() function now checks m->count > m->size - 1
instead of the previous method. The nvidia /proc entries use the old pattern.

Also fixes the addition of 'const' qualifier to dma_map_ops.get_required_mask.

Signed-off-by: Apollo Linux Team <dev@apollolinux.org>
---
diff --git a/kernel/nvidia/nv-procfs.c b/kernel/nvidia/nv-procfs.c
--- a/kernel/nvidia/nv-procfs.c
+++ b/kernel/nvidia/nv-procfs.c
@@ -1,4 +1,12 @@
+#include <linux/version.h>
+#include <linux/seq_file.h>
+
+#if LINUX_VERSION_CODE >= KERNEL_VERSION(6, 11, 0)
+/* seq_has_overflowed is now the canonical method */
+#define NV_SEQ_OVERFLOW(m) (seq_has_overflowed(m))
+#else
+/* Older kernels: check manually */
+#define NV_SEQ_OVERFLOW(m) ((m)->count == (m)->size)
+#endif
+
+/* const qualifier on dma_map_ops.get_required_mask in 6.11 */
+#if LINUX_VERSION_CODE >= KERNEL_VERSION(6, 11, 0)
+#define NV_DMA_GET_REQUIRED_MASK_CONST const
+#else
+#define NV_DMA_GET_REQUIRED_MASK_CONST
+#endif
